   <mods:abstract>Acknowledges letters of 10, 19 and 30 April and May 1. Congress still
            lacks quorum. Comments on importance of Constitutional Convention and need for a strong
            national government. Describes Adams' book as "valuable". Indian uprisings. Adams'
            resignation not yet reported to Congress. Delays of Congress on "almost every
            interesting subject" decried.</mods:abstract>
